subSubSection.paragraph:
Male genitalia
(
Fig. 2c,d
). Tergum IX subquadrate, wider than long, with proximal margin deeply emarginate, arcuate, apical margin with 2 small lobes (ninth tergal lobes) separated by a shallow concavity, each lobe bearing 6 setae; basal apodemes long, about same width as length (Fig. 5d). Gonocoxite long and slender, external length about 3.9 times its width at middle, with a poorly developed basal mesal lobe bearing 3 strong setae that are considerably larger than those nearby. Gonostylus 0.88 length of gonocoxite, apical 0.67 narrow, with about 6 small setae, ending in an apical straight and acute claw 0.2 gonostylus length. Proctiger triangular in tergal view, externally sclerotized and with a group of 5 small cercal setae near apex. Lateral plate of aedeagus simple, heavily sclerotized; phallosome short, parameres thumb-like with sclerotization at apex (
Fig. 2c
).
